1: On orders from the Guild, Alk and co. face off against a mysterious dragon that is terrorizing Palpebra.
3: Alk and co. manage to defeat the dragon, but its fallen form vanishes, leaving behind only the echoes of its roar. Sensing that they haven't seen the last of the mysterious beast, which has been dubbed "the Serpent" by the Guild, the companions prepare for a drawn-out fight.

Special Week, Silence Suzuka, and Gold Ship are in Tracen Academy's equipment room when they suddenly get whisked away to an unknown place. There, they meet up with Alk and come to the realization that they've ended up in another world.
2: The Umas are unsure if they'll find a way back to their home world. However, upon exploring the Kaleidoscope, they discover that the path back home is still open. They resolve to see the sights in this new world while they're here—only for a bunch of Voluntas Academy golems to go on a rampage and interrupt their plans.
4: After taking care of the rampaging golems, Alk and the others decide to watch the Palpebra Cup—which the three Umas have decided to race in as well. After the competition is over, the three are about to head home, when Gold Ship proudly declares she won't be returning, causing chaos on the scene.

1: On orders from the Guild, Alk and co. face off against a mysterious dragon that is terrorizing Palpebra.

Emilia and her group are suddenly dropped into an unfamiliar location, where they meet Alk and co. dispatching monsters. Emilia's group is in disbelief when they find out that no one there has heard of Lugunica, and they soon realize they've been stranded in a different world. The group stays at an inn but finds out the next morning that Subaru has been abducted during the night.
2: Alk and co. work together with Emilia's group to help rescue the kidnapped Subaru. Following the Witch's scent, they head to the Kaleidoscope. Ram and Emilia use their abilities to find Subaru, but the Dark Mage of the Kaleidoscope appears before them and summons foes for them to face.
4: Emilia's party defeats the creatures, but is trapped in the mage's spell. Subaru can't stand to see his friends in pain and manages to escape the mage. Subaru's group decides that they should set up a base in Palpebra while trying to figure out a way to return back to their home world.

1: A new serpent has awakened, and the Starview crew must defeat it before it lays waste to all Palpebra.
3: Ilma Talei is defeated, but still, many mysteries remain to be solved and many battles remain to be fought.

1: After learning about Halloween from Renoir, Dia excitedly dresses up and joins Alk and co. for the Halloween festival in Palpebra. They run into Corinna and kids from her orphanage, as well as Falsche. Falsche reveals that some of the festival-goers are actually undead.
2: Falsche and Pur Lilie explain that frenzied sprites have taken a magical pumpkin called a jack-o'-lantern and might be causing trouble somewhere. Meanwhile, two of the orphanage kids go missing. Alk and co. go to where they suspect the missing jack-o'-lantern might be, and find themselves battling it.
4: No matter how many times the group defeats the jack-o'-lantern, it revives itself using the lingering emotions of the dead. In order to soothe the negative emotions plaguing the poor pumpkin, Renoir takes Falsche to do some tinkering with Dia's systems. In the meantime, Alk, Nimbus, and Light hold the spooky foe off.
6: Dia gives a wonderful performance that calms the jack-o'-lantern, which disappears in a show of light. The missing kids are returned to Corinna, and one of them reveals that the undead had played with them and meant them no harm. Afterward, other kids from town ask the group for candy, but turn to tricks when they receive no treats.

1: Three young girls and a knight suddenly appear in the Kaleidoscope—pursued by a dangerous Arch Guardian. This group, all members of the "Gourmet Guild," joins forces with Alk and co. to take down this new menace.
3: The combined power of the two parties is enough to defeat the Arch Guardian. Realizing that this isn't a dream, the members of the Gourmet Guild resolve to continue their adventure by setting up a new chapter of their guild in Palpebra, all with the final goal of finding a way back home to Landosol.

1: A new serpent has awakened, and the Starview crew must defeat it before it lays waste to all Palpebra.
『反撃』の機会を失わない為にも街を死守する方針を固めたナオ達の下に、シブヤにも粛清者が現れたとの情報が入る。どうにかシブヤの人々を助けられないか考えたナオは、揺らぎを利用して迷宮を繋ぐことを提案し、陽動部隊は粛清者の気を引き始めるのだった
3: 迷宮を繋げるのに必要な『星の神器』を借りる為にベルセティアを探して迷宮に赴いたナオは、レオンに窮地を救われる。そこでレオンに救助されていたベルセティア達と遭遇したナオは、真摯な思いでベルセティアを説得し道を作るべく力を行使するのだった
4: シブヤで避難誘導を行っていたセイジは、メムラムに避難所を任せて住民達を連れて地下に向かっていた。地上では銀の森の連合を始めとした仲間達による防衛戦が繰り広げられており、地下ではセイジ達の目の前でナオが道を作り出すことに成功するのだった
7: 倒しても続々と天から現れる粛清者達の姿に絶望を感じていたスイゼン達は、突如『下』から放たれた陰の気を感じ取る。同じく呪いの力を感じ取ったナオ達は、チャルアがレシタール達と協力して呪いの力を全く別の力に変質させる瞬間を目撃するのだった
8: チャルアによって願いと形を与えられ街の各所に現れた残留思念達と、レシタールによる癒しと粛清者の『転生』封じによって一同は再び希望を見出す。街の人々がまだ誰も諦めていないことを知ったナオ達は、反撃の狼煙を上げるのだった

1: 星見の街でルナールからハロウィンの趣旨を聞いたディアは、新ボディに換装してアルク達とパルペブラを訪れる。そこで子供たちの引率をしていたコリーナ、用事の最中のファルチェと合流するが、ファルチェから仮装してる人の中に本物のアンデッドが混じっていることを告げられる
2: 騒動は、ある漂流物の実験中の暴走が原因と判明。怪しい反応を感知したファルチェとディアに従いアルク達は街外れにある墓地へと向かう。墓地に辿り着くと暴走した精霊とジャックオランタンを核とした亡霊がアルク達に襲い掛かってくる
4: 倒しても残留思念により再生してしまうジャックオランタン。ディアは歌を届けるためにルナールに自身の改造を頼む。ファルチェの協力も必要であると告げたルナールは、ディアの改造完了までアルク達に足止めを頼むのだった
6: ディアの歌を聞いたジャックオランタンは光に包まれ浄化される。街へ戻ったアルク達にケリーはお化けと遊ぶのは楽しかったと告げ、ファルチェにナイフの礼を言い和解する。そんなアルク達の元に子供達がイタズラをしにやってきて、みんなで笑い合いながらハロウィンを満喫するのだった

1: Instead of being greeted by bright lights and music for an upcoming concert, Franchouchou’s members awaken in an unfamiliar place. Upon finding refuge with Alk and co., they decide to be extra careful in keeping their zombie identities secret while living in this new world of Saga (aka Saloon Garden).
2: Tatsumi explains that Franchouchou can continue to save Saga by resuming idol activities in this new world. He arranges for Alk and co. to assist in the matter.
3: While handing out fliers in town to promote Franchouchou's upcoming concert, Alk and co. hear of monster sightings accompanying recent earthquakes. They end up as security detail for the concert, where a giant Romero shows up.
5: Franchouchou's members blast their accumulated Saga Power at Romero, cutting him down to size—literally. Tae's body parts accidentally go flying in every which direction, but they manage to make it seem like part of the show. With a successful concert behind them, the Franchouchou girls decide to resume their idol activities until they're able to return home to their own Saga.

1: While investigating a strange shift in the Kaleidoscope, Alk and co. run into two women fighting something they call primal beasts.
3: Zeta and Beatrix, visitors from another world, share all they know about primal beasts. The gang enlists the help of Palpebra's adventurers in a plan to send the primal beasts home.
5: The plan is successful, and the primal beasts are sent back to their original world. Zeta and Beatrix promise to come visit again before heading back home.
